    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 is a preserved example of the FD3S chassis, featuring the legendary 13B-REW rotary engine. The sequential twin-turbocharger system transitions seamlessly at 4,500 RPM, delivering linear power through the five-speed manual gearbox. Mechanical integrity is paramount; the cooling system has been overhauled with a high-capacity aluminum radiator to mitigate heat soak, and a recent compression test confirms healthy, consistent pulses across all rotor faces. The chassis remains rigid, utilizing its original double-wishbone suspension geometry and Torsen limited-slip differential for neutral cornering balance. Finished in factory-correct paint with an immaculate interior, this vehicle retains its longitudinal front-mid engine configuration and 50/50 weight distribution, offering a pure analog driving experience. Zero vacuum line leaks or wastegate fluctuations.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.3,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 45
    },
    {
